    <div id="feature" class="panel">
      <h1>Artemis: Genome Browser and Annotation Tool</h1>
      <div id="featureL">
        <p class="intro">
          Artemis is a free genome browser and annotation tool that allows visualisation of sequence features, next generation
          data and the results of analyses within the context of the sequence, and also its six-frame translation.
        </p>
        <p>
          Artemis is written in Java, and is available for UNIX, Macintosh and Windows systems. It can read EMBL and GENBANK
          database entries or sequence in FASTA, indexed FASTA or raw format. Other sequence features can be in EMBL, GENBANK or
          GFF format.
        </p>
        <h4>Links</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="/resources/software/act/">ACT</a> - a DNA sequence comparison viewer
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/resources/software/dnaplotter/">DNAPlotter</a> - makes circular and linear interactive plots
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="http://bamview.sourceforge.net/">BamView</a> - interactive display of read alignments in BAM data files
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div><div id="featureR"><div style="background-image:url(/resources/software/artemis/gfx/Pf3D7_01_RNA_Seq.png)"></div><p>[Genome Research Limited]</p></div>
    </div>
